ShortName: Ridge regularization
Concepts: A penalty as a second objective (fit the data AND keep coefficients small), $\lambda$ as the trade-off dial, shrinkage of coefficients toward 0 as $\lambda$ grows (the ridge path), why predictors must be standardized first, the bias–variance trade-off in words, the matrix form $(X^\top X + \lambda I)^{-1}$ that inverts for any $\lambda>0$, and lasso named as the cousin that zeroes coefficients
BuildsOn: [loss-functions-and-optimization](loss-functions-and-optimization/lesson.qmd), [model-fit-error-and-validation](model-fit-error-and-validation/lesson.qmd), [variance-structure-and-standardization](variance-structure-and-standardization/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
